# Backend (NestJS) Rules

## Structure

- Use NestJS modules, controllers, services pattern
- DTOs for request/response validation
- Environment variables via `@nestjs/config`

## API Conventions

- RESTful endpoints
- Use `@ApiTags`, `@ApiOperation` for Swagger when added
- Return consistent response shape: `{ data?, error?, message? }`

## Position/Game State

- Save player position: `lat`, `lng`, `userId`, `timestamp`
- Endpoint: `PATCH /players/:id/position` or `POST /game/save`
- Store in PostgreSQL (persistent), Redis (session cache optional)

## Error Handling

```typescript
// Prefer NestJS exceptions
throw new NotFoundException('Player not found');
throw new BadRequestException('Invalid coordinates');
```
